      〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
   , &c· Iohn 5.24.
Verify, verily I ſay vnto you, hee that heareth my Word, and beleeueth in him that ſent mee, hath euerlaſting life, and comes not into iudgement (as the Vulgar it ſelfe turnes it) but is paſſed from death vnto life;

                  Concil. Trid. Si quis dixerit in Sacram. Poenitentiae ad remiſſionem, &c. Anath. &c. Seſſ. 14. Gloſſ. Grat. de Poenit. diſt. 5. c. In poenitentia. Graeci ſolummodo Deo confitendum dicunt. de poenit. d. 1.

                  THe neceſſitie of a particular, ſecret, full, Sacramentall Confeſſion of all our ſins to a Prieſt; vpon paine of Non-remiſſion, is an Act or Inſtitution of the Romane Church, For, as for the Greeke Church it ownes not either the doctrine, or practice. So the Gloſſe of the Canon Law directly; Confeſsio apud Graecos, &c. Confeſſion is not not neceſſary amongſt the Grecians;


vnto whom no ſuch Tradition hath beene deriued.

Thus that diuine Father. With whom agrees Saint Ierome;
                     Hieron. in Eccleſ. 3. ad fin. 
                     Nec enim, poſſumus, &c. Neither can we (ſaith hee) when this life ſhall once be diſſolued, either enioy our owne labours, or know what ſhall bee done in the World afterwards.

And leaſt any man ſhould cauill that this ſtile is only cryed downe in the Biſhops of Conſtantinople, which yet might bee iuſtly claymed by the Biſhops of Rome; Gregorie himſelfe meetes with this thought, and anſwers beforehand;Nunquam pium virum huiuſmodi titulis vſum eſſe, &c. nullum praedeceſſorum meorum, &c. 
                  Nunquam pium virum, &c. that neuer any godly man, neuer any of his Predeceſſors vſed thoſe Titles; and, more then ſo, that whoſoeuer ſhall vſe this proud ſtile, hee is the very fore-runner of Antichriſt. If in a


fore-ſight of this vſurpation, Gregorie ſhould haue beene hired to haue ſpoken for vs, againſt the Pride of his following Succeſſours; he could not haue ſet a keener edge vpon his ſtile. Conſonant whereto, it is yet extant in the very Canon Law (as quoted by Gratian out of the Epiſtle of Pope Pelagius the ſecond) Vniuerſalis autem nec etiam Romanus Pontifex appelletur;Pelag. 2. omnibus Epiſcopis illicite à Ioanne & Decret. p. 1. diſt. 99. c. 4. Nullus, &c. Not the Biſhop of Rome himſelfe may bee called Vniuerſall;
